Capella Open Data IEEE Data Contest 2026

## Overview
The **2026 IEEE GRSS Data Analysis Contest**, organized by the **Image Analysis and Data Fusion (IADF) Technical Committee** and **Capella Space**, focuses on the operational reality of **commercial high-resolution SAR time series**.

Commercial SAR constellations can deliver dense temporal sampling, but stacks often have substantial variability in **imaging mode**, **incidence angle**, **look direction**, and **orbital geometry**. This variability complicates repeat-pass analysis, but also enables new approaches that exploit **temporal richness** and **observation diversity**.

This contest dataset provides **densely sampled, InSAR-compatible temporal stacks** of **very high-resolution X-band SAR imagery** across a wide range of imaging modes and viewing geometries.

---

## Dataset overview

### What’s included
- Multiple temporal stacks of **Capella Space X-band SAR** data
- Intended for:
  - time-series analysis
  - change detection
  - object/activity understanding
  - ML-based SAR analytics with emphasis on **robustness and generalization**

### Scale (current draft)
- ~**800 unique collects** across coordinated stacks (about a year)
- Potentially **17,000+ possible interferometric pairs**
- Some AOIs have **deep stacks** (e.g., **50+ images** over a year)

---

## Data access

### How is the data accessed?
Data is hosted in an **AWS S3 public bucket** via the Capella Space listing on the **Registry of Open Data on AWS**.

- [Dataset listing reference](https://stacindex.org/catalogs/capella-space-open-data#/6QUH7kZBffZNEnYuZuzZWv8D3vWA4TEeZvXZ5pubg4QY1ZAgGDY8dhJcDDxedMvN8d1Dwb)
- [STAC catalog](https://capella-open-data.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/stac/capella-open-data-ieee-data-contest/collection.json)
- [Capella Space Open Data felt.com map](https://felt.com/map/Capella-Space-Open-Data-bB24xsH3SuiUlpMdDbVRaA?loc=0,-20.53,1.94z) >> Select IEEE Data Contest 2026 layer

### Programatic access

`pip install pystac stac-asset[cli]`

`# 1 -- download all assets`
`import pystac`
`import stac_asset.blocking`

`collection = pystac.Collection.from_file("https://capella-open-data.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/stac/capella-open-data-ieee-data-contest/collection.json")`
`item_links = collection.get_item_links()`

`item = pystac.Item.from_file(item_links[0].absolute_href)`
`item = stac_asset.blocking.download_item(item)`


`# 2 -- download subset of assets`

`import pystac`
`import stac_asset.blocking`
`import os`

`collection = pystac.Collection.from_file("https://capella-open-data.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/stac/capella-open-data-ieee-data-contest/collection.json")`
`item_links = collection.get_item_links()`

`ASSETS_TO_DOWNLOAD = ["thumbnail", "preview"]`
`include_args = sum([['-i', asset] for asset in ASSETS_TO_DOWNLOAD], [])`

`cmd = ["stac-asset", "download", item_links[0].absolute_href] + include_args`
`os.system(' '.join(cmd))`
